The paper proposes a novel algorithm for supply chain design inspired by biological principles. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the algorithm handles supply networks with variables, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and cost minimization, which suggests that it may also belong to the computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-category.
